The article discusses the efforts of the Department of Defense (DOD) to eliminate sexual assault in the Armed Forces. The President has emphasized that sexual assault is a crime that undermines the honor and integrity of the military. The DOD, including the senior civilian leadership and each of the Services, has been working intensively to fulfill the President's call to action. Secretary of Defense Hagel has announced new Executive Actions to address the issue. While these initiatives are substantial, they are seen as just a step towards eliminating sexual assault from the military. The President expects sustained effort in the future to protect those who serve and hold offenders accountable. The article concludes by stating that no member of the military should have to experience the pain and degradation of sexual assault.